SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3431
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE WEST.
7399H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 21, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to certain employees
of the general assembly.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 21, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 21.153, to read as follows:
21.153. Subject to appropriation, partisan employees of the general assembly
2 including, but not limited to, legislator assistants, policy directors, and chiefs of staff
3 shall receive a pay increase if the employee has or obtains a degree from an accredited
4 college or university. The pay increase shall be as follows:
5 (1) For staff with a bachelor's degree, three percent; and
6 (2) For staff with a master's or doctoral degree, six percent.
7
8 An employee shall receive only the increase for the highest degree he or she holds.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

